## Attribute builders

When you instrument an AWS call by hand, `autotel-aws/attributes` builds the
canonical span attributes for you. `AWS_ATTRS` holds the semantic-convention
keys; the `build*` helpers turn a service operation into the attribute object.

```typescript
import { buildLambdaAttributes, buildDynamoDBAttributes } from 'autotel-aws/attributes';

span.setAttributes(
  buildLambdaAttributes({
    functionName: 'my-handler',
    functionVersion: '$LATEST',
    awsRequestId: context.awsRequestId,
    coldStart: true,
  }),
);
```

Builders exist for Lambda, the SDK, DynamoDB, S3, SQS, SNS, Kinesis, Step
Functions, and EventBridge.

